00-meta/beestgraph/Mobile Qualification Review Page.md

## Title
Mobile Qualification Review Page

## Recommendation Summary

### Intent Assessment
Design spec for a mobile-friendly web page for reviewing, editing, and approving qualification queue items, replacing verbose Telegram messages with minimal pings + web links.

### Categorization Changes
- **ZETT**: "none (status: qualifying)" → "content_stage: evergreen" (Original design document with UI mockups and API specs. Evergreen. Missing content_stage field.)
- **TREE**: "meta/tools" → "meta/beestgraph/architecture, technology/web/frontend" (This is a beestgraph feature spec with frontend UI design. meta/tools is too generic.)
- **GRAPH**: "Likely has Document node" → "Ensure edges to Qualification Pipeline, Telegram as Capture Source, Content Types Taxonomy. Mobile Review and Qualification UI should be Concept nodes." (Design spec should connect to related pipeline docs.)

### Metadata Issues
Missing content_stage field. Status qualifying — appropriate since this is a design spec not yet implemented. Missing created_at/updated_at. The ASCII mockup is a nice design artifact. API routes are well-defined.

### Suggested Interlinks
- [[[[Pluggable Notification and Review Channels]]]]
- [[[[Beestgraph Knowledge Standard (BKS)]]]]
- [[[[3D Knowledge Graph Viewer]]]]
- [[[[CalDAV Integration]]]]

### Enrichment
Mobile-first design remains dominant in 2026 with over 60% of web traffic from mobile. Modern queue management systems use QR codes and web-based check-in. The design pattern of minimal notification + rich web review page is widely validated. Consider implementing progressive web app (PWA) features for offline queue review.

